WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.169
Previously on will Trent…

2
00:00:03.462 --> 00:00:05.482
Got to the point where I'd look
in the mirror and didn't know

3
00:00:05.506 --> 00:00:06.816
who I was looking at.

4
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:09.694
Then Gina. she found a meeting
that I could go to. Talking helps.

5
00:00:09.718 --> 00:00:13.597
The best part of this drink is
it comes with a fun umbrella.

6
00:00:14.973 --> 00:00:16.784
- Antonio!
- I'll check the back.

7
00:00:16.808 --> 00:00:17.869
Antonio!

8
00:00:17.893 --> 00:00:18.953
He's gone.

9
00:00:18.977 --> 00:00:20.788
James ulster's been
dead for nearly two months.

10
00:00:20.812 --> 00:00:22.040
That's what you think.

11
00:00:22.064 --> 00:00:24.501
I got a letter. That's how he talked to me.

12
00:00:24.525 --> 00:00:26.377
That's how he talked to all of us.

13
00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:28.463
If I had nothing to do
with sending those letters…

14
00:00:28.487 --> 00:00:31.841
Then there's someone else who knows
about Antonio. my mother. everything.

15
00:00:31.865 --> 00:00:33.665
- Where's my uncle?
- Guess you'll never know.

16
00:00:34.159 --> 00:00:35.303
Where is he?

17
00:00:35.327 --> 00:00:36.387
What happened?

18
00:00:36.411 --> 00:00:38.473
Spiders. Poison.

19
00:00:38.497 --> 00:00:42.376
Hey. hey. Will. stay with me. Help
is on the way. Will. stay with me.

20
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:50.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

21
00:00:58.934 --> 00:01:00.102
Ang.

22
00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:03.313
Hey. you're awake.

23
00:01:04.398 --> 00:01:05.542
How do you feel?

24
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:07.985
Weird.

25
00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:10.088
Dizzy.

26
00:01:10.112 --> 00:01:12.799
Yeah. they gave you
antivenom for the spider bites

27
00:01:12.823 --> 00:01:16.952
and a sedative because
you were in a state.

28
00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:25.002
Yeah. you were trying to pull
out your iv. go after Antonio.

29
00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:29.715
- What do you know?
- What we know is that

30
00:01:30.215 --> 00:01:32.634
Adelaide was spotted in Brazil.

31
00:01:33.552 --> 00:01:35.012
We don't know if he's with her.

32
00:01:35.804 --> 00:01:38.366
The FBI has. like. a whole team on it…

33
00:01:38.390 --> 00:01:40.952
…and they're doing their FBI thing.

34
00:01:40.976 --> 00:01:44.330
I need to… I gotta… I gotta
go do something to help.

35
00:01:44.354 --> 00:01:45.790
- Hey.
- Can you get me out of here?

36
00:01:45.814 --> 00:01:48.167
Will. you just woke up five seconds ago.

37
00:01:48.191 --> 00:01:51.421
Can you please take some
time to recover from almost dying

38
00:01:51.445 --> 00:01:53.155
before you beat yourself up again?

39
00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:58.177
- He's my family. ang.
- I know.

40
00:01:58.201 --> 00:02:01.997
I know. And they will tell me
as soon as they learn anything.

41
00:02:02.581 --> 00:02:03.749
They're gonna find him.

42
00:02:08.712 --> 00:02:09.713
Did you sleep here?

43
00:02:10.297 --> 00:02:11.298
Of course.

44
00:02:12.841 --> 00:02:14.176
You're my family.

45
00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:21.868
Let me get somebody
to handle those straps.

46
00:02:21.892 --> 00:02:23.268
You must be starving.

47
00:02:23.769 --> 00:02:26.396
I'll have Seth make someone
bring you the good meat loaf.

48
00:02:27.439 --> 00:02:29.042
Is there such a thing?

49
00:02:29.066 --> 00:02:31.669
Well. trust me. you
don't want the bad one.

50
00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:36.007
So you're the one who found him?

51
00:02:36.031 --> 00:02:40.553
Yeah. this morning I noticed the
door was wide open. found him inside.

52
00:02:40.577 --> 00:02:42.847
Now I gotta do a deep-clean.

53
00:02:42.871 --> 00:02:44.456
Yeah. that sounds like a hassle.

54
00:02:45.123 --> 00:02:46.434
You got a name?

55
00:02:46.458 --> 00:02:48.061
No. he paid cash.

56
00:02:48.085 --> 00:02:49.294
Did you get his ID?

57
00:02:49.878 --> 00:02:52.130
This look like the kind
of place that checks ids?

58
00:02:53.674 --> 00:02:55.318
Can't find the guy's wallet anywhere.

59
00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:56.778
Door's wide open.

60
00:02:56.802 --> 00:02:58.679
Anyone could have lifted it after the fact.

61
00:02:59.888 --> 00:03:03.266
And he definitely had money. The guy's
sweater's worth more than my mortgage.

62
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:08.438
Okay. so headphones. keyboard.

63
00:03:10.107 --> 00:03:12.567
This notebook's full of music stuff.

64
00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:14.837
Music stuff?

65
00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:16.964
Yeah. Franklin. music stuff.

66
00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:20.325
Sheet music. musical
notations. composing.

67
00:03:21.118 --> 00:03:23.304
Why would a rich guy
work from this dump?

68
00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.474
Drugs? We got some white
powder here. Looks like cocaine.

69
00:03:26.498 --> 00:03:29.376
- Yeah.
- And what do we have here? Adderall.

70
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:31.229
Is there a name on the bottle?

71
00:03:31.253 --> 00:03:32.855
Label's torn. Hard to make it out.

72
00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:34.899
Hey. let's get this. logged and bagged.

73
00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:38.444
So. doing a little coke. tickling the ivories.

74
00:03:38.468 --> 00:03:40.679
Sounds like a fun night till he got shot.

75
00:03:49.521 --> 00:03:50.623
Did Cooper teach you that?

76
00:03:50.647 --> 00:03:53.358
Cooper has nowhere near my skills.

77
00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:55.920
Hey.

78
00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:59.090
this keyboard case says
"property of Atlanta city orchestra."

79
00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:01.199
No.

80
00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:03.118
I know who this is.

81
00:04:03.618 --> 00:04:04.762
Who?

82
00:04:04.786 --> 00:04:08.015
It's Ronaldo benetti. the conductor
of the Atlanta city orchestra.

83
00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:09.124
Why "no"?

84
00:04:10.959 --> 00:04:14.105
'Cause a man is dead. and
every life lost is a tragedy.

85
00:04:14.129 --> 00:04:15.481
Yeah.

86
00:04:15.505 --> 00:04:16.631
But really. why "no"?

87
00:04:17.215 --> 00:04:18.425
I'm a patron of the arts.

88
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:21.761
- Since when?
- You know.

89
00:04:22.929 --> 00:04:24.073
I go to the symphony.

90
00:04:24.097 --> 00:04:27.535
Why are you acting so weird right now?
Since when do you go to the symphony?

91
00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:30.979
During my personal private life.
which you know nothing about.

92
00:04:32.731 --> 00:04:34.775
Do we have to go to symphony hall now?

93
00:04:35.609 --> 00:04:37.920
Seems like we do. Yeah.

94
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:44.409
We've got two eggs. half a bell
pepper. and some wilted spinach.

95
00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:48.371
I could make you an omelet.

96
00:04:49.998 --> 00:04:51.374
I'm not hungry.

97
00:04:52.209 --> 00:04:53.478
I just had meat loaf.

98
00:04:53.502 --> 00:04:55.253
Okay. How about some tea?

99
00:04:56.379 --> 00:04:57.964
Yeah. sure.

100
00:05:18.652 --> 00:05:20.070
I hate this floor.

101
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:23.448
Yeah. me too.

102
00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:25.992
Okay. let's get rid of the floor.

103
00:05:30.664 --> 00:05:33.559
Is there a plan or are
we just deconstructing?

104
00:05:35.001 --> 00:05:37.522
You know. that-that's a good question.

105
00:05:37.546 --> 00:05:41.859
How about you. go
to the hardware store?

106
00:05:41.883 --> 00:05:45.530
And grab some-some linoleum samples?

107
00:05:45.554 --> 00:05:47.448
Okay.

108
00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:48.723
Come on. Betty.

109
00:05:49.432 --> 00:05:50.600
Let's go shopping.

110
00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:13.206
There. there.

111
00:06:15.876 --> 00:06:17.436
I'm so over you.

112
00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:21.440
As horrible as this floor is.

113
00:06:21.464 --> 00:06:23.592
I think our efforts would
be better spent elsewhere.

114
00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:29.824
You really think it's wise to leave
the search for Adelaide to the FBI?

115
00:06:29.848 --> 00:06:33.602
There is no "our."

116
00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:35.687
All right? It's all your fault.

117
00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:40.251
I can't believe you were
allowed to procreate.

118
00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:41.752
Look on the bright side.

119
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.588
Who's better qualified than you

120
00:06:43.612 --> 00:06:47.157
to track down a deranged
James ulster obsessive?

121
00:06:47.741 --> 00:06:49.868
Come on. will. Where should we start?

122
00:06:51.369 --> 00:06:52.412
Her mother.

123
00:06:57.292 --> 00:06:58.335
I'm doing better.

124
00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:00.587
Fewer flashbacks.

125
00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:03.298
But it's hard.

126
00:07:04.174 --> 00:07:05.550
I still don't feel like myself.

127
00:07:06.801 --> 00:07:08.303
I'm used to being in control.

128
00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:12.849
I'm the one who
protects the people I love.

129
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:20.273
You know. lately I've been
thinking about buildings.

130
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:24.527
You know how the ones
built with some give…

131
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:27.364
…they're the ones that
survive earthquakes.

132
00:07:28.073 --> 00:07:30.408
But the ones that are rigid…

133
00:07:32.702 --> 00:07:34.412
They're the ones that just crumble.

134
00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:37.725
I have to believe that.

135
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:41.878
finding a way to move with
the ground shifting under me…

136
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.549
It's the only way to survive.

137
00:07:50.512 --> 00:07:51.572
Hey.

138
00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:54.516
That was really beautiful. what you said.

139
00:07:55.642 --> 00:07:56.893
Thank you. Casey.

140
00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:02.249
- Have you seen your ex's truck this week?
- Couple of times.

141
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:04.001
Still parked down at
the end of the block?

142
00:08:04.025 --> 00:08:05.878
Hundred yards to the inch.

143
00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:10.466
Well. if he comes any
closer. you call me.

144
00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:13.052
I'll get his ass on violating
that restraining order.

145
00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:16.555
Wow. You weren't kidding when
you said you were protective.

146
00:08:18.665 --> 00:08:19.791
I like it.

147
00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:22.085
I like seeing you alive.

148
00:08:23.002 --> 00:08:28.049
Do you want to have
dinner tonight at my place?

149
00:08:31.261 --> 00:08:32.530
I'll bring the wine.

150
00:08:40.729 --> 00:08:43.916
Hey. guys. The gbi just got tagged in.

151
00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:46.252
Apparently Ronaldo
benetti is kind of a big deal.

152
00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:48.754
Yeah. Franklin's a big fan.

153
00:08:48.778 --> 00:08:50.631
There's something weird
going on. and he won't tell me.

154
00:08:50.655 --> 00:08:52.633
But he did do a whitening
strip on the way over.

155
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:54.719
What happened to partner code. man?

156
00:08:54.743 --> 00:08:55.970
You got anything new for us?

157
00:08:55.994 --> 00:08:58.014
Yeah. I talked to Pete on the way out.

158
00:08:58.038 --> 00:09:00.433
Cause of death is a gunshot. but get this.

159
00:09:00.457 --> 00:09:02.000
victim had postmortem bruising.

160
00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:05.021
So whoever did this shot
him and then beat him up?

161
00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:06.171
They really hated this guy.

162
00:09:14.721 --> 00:09:17.450
- We should interview all these people.
- Yep.

163
00:09:17.474 --> 00:09:18.933
I'll take the trumpet player.

164
00:09:21.352 --> 00:09:23.581
Sorry. is there no one else
who can do this interview?

165
00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:25.791
It's stressful enough that
Ronaldo was apparently murdered.

166
00:09:25.815 --> 00:09:26.876
and now you show up.

167
00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:28.169
It's just business. Leon.

168
00:09:28.193 --> 00:09:30.671
Do you take prescription medication?

169
00:09:30.695 --> 00:09:32.506
You know that I do. Why is that relevant?

170
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.991
'Cause we found a bottle of
Adderall at the crime scene.

171
00:09:35.575 --> 00:09:38.953
and the letters on the label
seem to match your name.

172
00:09:40.413 --> 00:09:44.185
Okay. look. Ronaldo. he
was under a ton of pressure.

173
00:09:44.209 --> 00:09:45.686
He was having trouble
getting work done.

174
00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:48.105
so he asked if I could share
some of my meds with him.

175
00:09:48.129 --> 00:09:49.732
So I gave him a few pills.

176
00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:51.192
What kind of pressure?

177
00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:53.736
We have a big performance coming up.

178
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.346
We're doing Ronaldo's
original composition.

179
00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:58.616
So. he was a composer too?

180
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:01.202
He talked about it a lot.

181
00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:03.329
This was the first one
he actually finished.

182
00:10:03.353 --> 00:10:05.873
But it took forever for
Ronaldo to show it to us.

183
00:10:05.897 --> 00:10:08.834
He was acting more and more erratic.

184
00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:11.879
Everyone was starting to
freak out. especially Claudia.

185
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:15.132
- Who's Claudia?
- The executive director of the symphony.

186
00:10:15.156 --> 00:10:17.927
Claudia was afraid that we
would have nothing to play.

187
00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:19.470
that we'd have to call the whole thing off.

188
00:10:19.494 --> 00:10:23.224
But then. finally… …after
disappearing for. like. 24 hours.

189
00:10:23.248 --> 00:10:26.209
Ronaldo showed up
yesterday. said he was finished.

190
00:10:27.293 --> 00:10:29.522
And it's annoyingly brilliant.

191
00:10:29.546 --> 00:10:31.190
How long is this gonna take?

192
00:10:31.214 --> 00:10:34.151
Lila. honey. let's let the
detectives do their job.

193
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.946
Tom. you're always
trying to manage me. Just…

194
00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:37.971
I-I need a cigarette.

195
00:10:38.513 --> 00:10:39.824
- That's fine.
- Thank you.

196
00:10:39.848 --> 00:10:42.243
Pippa. are we still performing or what?

197
00:10:42.267 --> 00:10:44.286
I don't know.

198
00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:46.372
- Is your solo ready?
- Yes. of course it is.

199
00:10:46.396 --> 00:10:47.748
Brass. on the other hand. mess.

200
00:10:47.772 --> 00:10:49.583
She hums Ronaldo's soaring melody

201
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:53.486
- as she dozes beside me at night.
- But who's going to conduct it. Tom?

202
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:58.384
I'm very sorry. We're both very upset.

203
00:10:58.408 --> 00:10:59.868
- Are you coming?
- Yeah.

204
00:11:03.371 --> 00:11:05.081
Where were you last night. Leon?

205
00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:07.935
You have to answer my
question. You're a suspect.

206
00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:09.019
I'm a suspect?

207
00:11:09.043 --> 00:11:11.647
You're not not a suspect.
You gave a dead man drugs.

208
00:11:11.671 --> 00:11:13.566
- Adderall.
- It's a controlled substance.

209
00:11:13.590 --> 00:11:15.734
Seriously. Franklin.
come on. you know me.

210
00:11:15.758 --> 00:11:17.820
You know. I thought I did.

211
00:11:17.844 --> 00:11:20.531
- Be honest. Are you punishing me?
- Just give me an alibi.

212
00:11:20.555 --> 00:11:22.473
I was at my boyfriend's all night.

213
00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:25.953
- Boyfriend?
- There's a camera in the lobby

214
00:11:25.977 --> 00:11:27.228
that you can check.

215
00:11:29.397 --> 00:11:31.458
Now just ask me what
you really want to know.

216
00:11:31.482 --> 00:11:34.277
Well… …I mean. I am curious.

217
00:11:34.944 --> 00:11:36.404
Four months of happy dating.

218
00:11:36.988 --> 00:11:39.991
I had a drawer at your place.
you had a toothbrush at mine.

219
00:11:40.575 --> 00:11:41.802
Why did you ghost me?

220
00:11:46.331 --> 00:11:47.582
"Not funny."

221
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:50.060
- He said that?
- I know I made him laugh before.

222
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:52.563
I just can't think of any
specific moment right now.

223
00:11:52.587 --> 00:11:54.422
- but I know I did.
- Pippa!

224
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:56.424
Pippa!

225
00:11:57.508 --> 00:12:00.529
- Where is pippa?
- Claudia. hi.

226
00:12:00.553 --> 00:12:02.031
Did you hear? How are you?

227
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:04.849
Yes. it's horrible. I have
grief counselors on their way.

228
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:09.354
Anyone who needs to avail themselves
can. but please don't leave the building.

229
00:12:10.146 --> 00:12:11.481
We have to rehearse.

230
00:12:12.315 --> 00:12:13.942
We're not canceling the show?

231
00:12:14.525 --> 00:12:17.713
- Absolutely not.
- I'm sorry. Why not?

232
00:12:17.737 --> 00:12:19.572
It's not what Ronaldo would want.

233
00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:22.450
We owe it to him to let
his Magnum opus be heard.

234
00:12:24.702 --> 00:12:26.847
Pippa. we need a conductor.

235
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:29.791
Can you do it?

236
00:12:30.667 --> 00:12:31.668
Yes.

237
00:12:33.544 --> 00:12:35.797
Good. Go tell everyone.

238
00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:40.444
Hi. Sorry about that.

239
00:12:40.468 --> 00:12:43.572
Claudia sobinsky. executive
director. How can I help?

240
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:45.598
Well. we need to see Ronaldo's office.

241
00:12:47.183 --> 00:12:48.953
- Right this way.
- Thank you.

242
00:12:48.977 --> 00:12:51.455
Sounds like Ronaldo
was acting erratic recently.

243
00:12:51.479 --> 00:12:54.941
I've known Ronaldo for 25
years. since our music school days.

244
00:12:55.608 --> 00:12:57.086
I'd never seen him like this.

245
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.486
It was this composition.

246
00:12:59.112 --> 00:13:02.007
I told him he was
already a great conductor.

247
00:13:02.031 --> 00:13:05.761
He didn't need to compose.
but… …he wouldn't listen.

248
00:13:05.785 --> 00:13:08.180
He just put so much
pressure on himself.

249
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:10.432
How was it that it came down
to the last second like this?

250
00:13:10.456 --> 00:13:13.394
He insisted I schedule his debut
as the highlight of our season.

251
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:16.522
even hinged his entire
contract renegotiation on it.

252
00:13:16.546 --> 00:13:18.399
And then. once everything was signed.

253
00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:21.360
it turned out he hadn't even written it yet.

254
00:13:21.384 --> 00:13:23.529
That's why he didn't want pippa to see it.

255
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:25.656
I've been close to a heart attack waiting.

256
00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:29.660
But yesterday. Ronaldo showed
up with a completed chamber piece.

257
00:13:29.684 --> 00:13:32.645
and it was everything he'd promised.

258
00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:34.897
It was stunning.

259
00:13:35.481 --> 00:13:36.961
Ronaldo have issues with anyone here?

260
00:13:38.192 --> 00:13:40.528
He was a giant pain in the ass. but.

261
00:13:41.738 --> 00:13:42.822
he was our maestro.

262
00:13:44.198 --> 00:13:45.950
Everyone worshipped him.

263
00:13:47.410 --> 00:13:50.580
Yeah. I can relate. I play a little myself.

264
00:13:51.372 --> 00:13:53.726
Really. man? Every time?

265
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:56.228
You know what. don't do
that. Please don't do that.

266
00:13:59.255 --> 00:14:00.381
That's weird.

267
00:14:07.597 --> 00:14:09.825
I guess someone here
didn't worship Ronaldo.

268
00:14:09.849 --> 00:14:10.892
At all.

269
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:15.873
I already told the FBI.

270
00:14:15.897 --> 00:14:18.000
I don't know where Adelaide is.

271
00:14:18.024 --> 00:14:23.797
No. of course. but… …if you
could think of anything else.

272
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:26.508
anything at all that
might help us find her.

273
00:14:26.532 --> 00:14:27.801
we'd appreciate it.

274
00:14:27.825 --> 00:14:34.457
There was always
something off with that girl.

275
00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:37.519
Chip off the old block. Maybe
I was wrong to reject her.

276
00:14:37.543 --> 00:14:40.755
Speaking of. all those
letters Adelaide sent me.

277
00:14:41.464 --> 00:14:44.610
I sent them back unopened.

278
00:14:44.634 --> 00:14:47.178
Maybe they're around here somewhere.

279
00:14:48.054 --> 00:14:53.101
I tried to set Adelaide on the right path.

280
00:14:54.227 --> 00:15:00.858
But no matter how long I
kept her in the wardrobe.

281
00:15:01.609 --> 00:15:03.003
nothing happened.

282
00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:04.028
The wardrobe?

283
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:10.576
It's our little nickname for time-out.

284
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:14.640
I had to send her there
when she misbehaved.

285
00:15:14.664 --> 00:15:16.683
Bad mommy.

286
00:15:16.707 --> 00:15:18.977
…discipline your children…

287
00:15:19.001 --> 00:15:20.813
I don't know why I had
sex with this woman.

288
00:15:26.342 --> 00:15:29.613
Ms. Trevens. could I… could I
trouble you for a glass of water?

289
00:15:31.347 --> 00:15:32.473
Thank you.

290
00:16:01.627 --> 00:16:03.546
Now. this is twisted.

291
00:16:04.213 --> 00:16:05.423
Even for me.

292
00:16:06.924 --> 00:16:08.426
She was just a kid.

293
00:16:10.011 --> 00:16:12.114
I should arrest this lady for child abuse.

294
00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:15.308
No. keep your eye on the ball.
You haven't looked in there yet.

295
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:23.458
You're welcome.

296
00:16:23.482 --> 00:16:24.626
Shut up.

297
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:26.527
You're me. Stop taking credit.

298
00:16:31.157 --> 00:16:35.411
This is you entering
Ronaldo's office three days ago.

299
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:38.807
We know you destroyed his piano.

300
00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:41.143
We saw the damage.
Now that is real hatred.

301
00:16:41.167 --> 00:16:44.670
You've been assistant
conductor for what. six years now?

302
00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.816
It's a long time to play second fiddle.

303
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:50.903
It's not easy to stand on the sidelines.
watch somebody else live your dreams.

304
00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:52.696
I mean. it makes sense to resent him.

305
00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:55.991
Sometimes that's easier than admitting
maybe you don't have what it takes.

306
00:16:56.015 --> 00:16:57.475
I do have what it takes.

307
00:16:58.351 --> 00:17:00.871
The passion. the focus. the commitment.

308
00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:03.332
That bastard tried to
break me. but I'm still here.

309
00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:08.462
Yeah. Yeah. you are. front and
center on the symphony's biggest night.

310
00:17:08.486 --> 00:17:10.464
What? No.

311
00:17:10.488 --> 00:17:11.822
It's finally working out for you.

312
00:17:13.032 --> 00:17:16.261
Okay. fine. I destroyed the
piano. but I didn't kill him.

313
00:17:16.285 --> 00:17:18.412
Yeah. well. you certainly killed that piano.

314
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:22.893
What exactly did Ronaldo
do to make you so angry?

315
00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:27.296
He belittled my conducting. the
way I dressed. my music knowledge.

316
00:17:27.922 --> 00:17:30.651
For years. he told me I'd
never make it as a conductor

317
00:17:30.675 --> 00:17:32.426
and refused to give
me a recommendation.

318
00:17:34.595 --> 00:17:36.931
He knew about the piano. by the way.

319
00:17:37.515 --> 00:17:40.536
When he saw what I'd
done. he was impressed.

320
00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:42.770
He said it was about
time I showed some teeth.

321
00:17:44.897 --> 00:17:47.000
I swear I didn't kill him.

322
00:17:47.024 --> 00:17:49.902
I-I didn't want to get the job
this way. I wanted to earn it.

323
00:17:51.737 --> 00:17:55.050
Is there anything you can tell us
about Ronaldo's disappearance

324
00:17:55.074 --> 00:17:56.969
the day before he
delivered the composition?

325
00:17:58.119 --> 00:18:01.431
All-all I know is when I asked
how he managed to finish the piece.

326
00:18:01.455 --> 00:18:03.791
he told me he'd found his muse.

327
00:18:05.251 --> 00:18:06.645
Any idea who he was referring to?

328
00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:10.107
No. I just figured that
meant he'd gotten laid.

329
00:18:10.131 --> 00:18:12.216
Guy was hornier than a jackrabbit.

330
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:16.863
Hey. they found
Ronaldo's car abandoned.

331
00:18:16.887 --> 00:18:18.907
It's being towed to the
impound lot. Let's go.

332
00:18:35.031 --> 00:18:36.032
Hey.

333
00:18:36.866 --> 00:18:38.868
Yeah. I thought you might be working.

334
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:41.888
- Brought szechuan.
- Where's Seth?

335
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:45.684
He is drinking a nonalcoholic beer
and watching a documentary on dunkirk.

336
00:18:45.708 --> 00:18:49.337
Hi. baby. I missed you. Come here.

337
00:18:50.254 --> 00:18:53.799
Help me take this food to the
dining table. will you? Yeah?

338
00:18:54.508 --> 00:18:55.777
So what do you got?

339
00:18:55.801 --> 00:18:58.530
Adelaide's letters to ulster in prison.

340
00:19:00.556 --> 00:19:03.076
You want to read 'em
to me over egg rolls?

341
00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:04.268
Perfect night.

342
00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:07.063
What's up with your kitchen?

343
00:19:07.855 --> 00:19:10.816
I-It's nothing. It… don't worry about it.

344
00:19:13.235 --> 00:19:17.466
"She is stupid and never listens
to me. I hate her. I hate her.

345
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:22.137
I wish you'd never met her.
Please show me how to kill her.

346
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:24.848
I'll do anything. Your daughter. Adelaide."

347
00:19:24.872 --> 00:19:27.184
You say you had a
flirtation with this woman?

348
00:19:27.208 --> 00:19:29.394
We were in the jungle.

349
00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:32.314
It was very hot and. my guard was down.

350
00:19:32.338 --> 00:19:34.423
Look. I've been very vulnerable lately.

351
00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:41.740
Adelaide never stood a chance.

352
00:19:41.764 --> 00:19:43.158
Abusive mother. no friends.

353
00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:45.893
She could've been us. She could've.

354
00:19:46.894 --> 00:19:49.647
But we had each other.

355
00:19:54.652 --> 00:19:56.570
- You changed your hair.
- Yeah.

356
00:19:57.988 --> 00:19:59.115
Controlling what I can.

357
00:20:01.117 --> 00:20:02.410
I like it.

358
00:20:04.078 --> 00:20:08.433
It makes sense that
Adelaide would start a network.

359
00:20:08.457 --> 00:20:10.644
Other people who fell
through the cracks like her.

360
00:20:10.668 --> 00:20:14.880
That network is the best way
to get to Antonio. Has to be.

361
00:20:16.924 --> 00:20:19.093
I gotta take a run at Jeb oswald.

362
00:20:20.845 --> 00:20:23.657
- Any advice?
- You're not gonna scare him.

363
00:20:23.681 --> 00:20:25.808
You're not gonna get
through to him with logic.

364
00:20:26.767 --> 00:20:29.729
The only person he wants
to talk to is James ulster.

365
00:20:33.107 --> 00:20:34.358
I can work with that.

366
00:20:36.026 --> 00:20:39.548
I don't understand… wait.
get your hands off my dishes.

367
00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:41.633
Gosh. you don't know
how to relax. do you?

368
00:20:41.657 --> 00:20:44.243
Let me take care of you
for once. Go. Go away.

369
00:20:44.827 --> 00:20:47.639
Okay. okay. Bossy.

370
00:20:47.663 --> 00:20:49.224
Takes one to know one.

371
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:51.143
You might be right about that.

372
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:56.440
I took that when I was 18.

373
00:20:56.464 --> 00:21:00.610
I had nothing better to do than
follow a dirt road. see where it took me.

374
00:21:00.634 --> 00:21:02.612
I really thought I was a
photographer with that one.

375
00:21:02.636 --> 00:21:05.490
Who you telling?

376
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:08.660
I took a pottery class once and
could have sworn I was a professional.

377
00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:11.937
I always said I'd go back. But…

378
00:21:13.481 --> 00:21:14.607
Then I met Dallas and…

379
00:21:16.358 --> 00:21:18.194
Best-laid plans.

380
00:21:22.823 --> 00:21:23.824
Look.

381
00:21:25.075 --> 00:21:26.845
With everything you've
been going through…

382
00:21:26.869 --> 00:21:28.829
Okay. stop worrying about me.

383
00:21:29.955 --> 00:21:31.749
Start thinking about what you want.

384
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:44.345
Do you want this?

385
00:21:57.483 --> 00:21:59.735
How about this?

386
00:22:23.008 --> 00:22:27.847
Now. is this the beer
bottle or the coffee pot?

387
00:22:31.475 --> 00:22:32.810
Coffee pot.

388
00:22:37.773 --> 00:22:39.650
You're incredibly brave. Casey.

389
00:22:49.660 --> 00:22:50.661
So are you.

390
00:23:04.383 --> 00:23:07.362
Don't bother. Amanda.
He always gets away with it.

391
00:23:12.600 --> 00:23:14.760
Better have a damn good
reason for hauling me in here.

392
00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:16.997
Why don't you take a seat?

393
00:23:17.021 --> 00:23:18.772
Why don't you tell me why I'm here?

394
00:23:21.191 --> 00:23:24.254
You threw a rock through your
estranged wife's window last night.

395
00:23:24.278 --> 00:23:27.674
That's vandalism. harassment. and
a violation of your restraining order.

396
00:23:27.698 --> 00:23:29.718
I wasn't anywhere near
that bitch's house last night.

397
00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:31.678
I know you've been
parking on Casey's street.

398
00:23:31.702 --> 00:23:32.846
trying to intimidate her.

399
00:23:32.870 --> 00:23:34.180
I can park wherever I want.

400
00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:36.766
I know everything
you put Casey through.

401
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:39.084
I know every bruise and every scar.

402
00:23:40.044 --> 00:23:41.211
But that's over now.

403
00:23:42.379 --> 00:23:44.065
You need to leave her alone.

404
00:23:44.089 --> 00:23:45.799
You have no proof. do you?

405
00:23:47.551 --> 00:23:50.387
Looks like you're the one
who's trying to intimidate me.

406
00:23:51.305 --> 00:23:53.432
And I won't be intimidated.

407
00:23:54.475 --> 00:23:57.311
I think this interview is over.

408
00:24:00.230 --> 00:24:02.792
I met a million guys like you.

409
00:24:02.816 --> 00:24:05.754
Men who think they're untouchable.

410
00:24:05.778 --> 00:24:09.174
You think you can lay your hands on
anybody you want and get away with it.

411
00:24:09.198 --> 00:24:12.034
Not this time.

412
00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:25.857
Geez. faith. this car is
almost as messy as yours is.

413
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:29.027
- What's with you creative types?
- Yeah. it's organized chaos.

414
00:24:29.051 --> 00:24:30.111
You know. the thing is…

415
00:24:30.135 --> 00:24:32.530
And look. I don't want to
come across as defensive.

416
00:24:32.554 --> 00:24:34.866
but I am infinitely funnier
than Leon ever was.

417
00:24:34.890 --> 00:24:36.952
Yeah. you're funny. It's. like. your thing.

418
00:24:36.976 --> 00:24:38.161
What do you mean. my thing?

419
00:24:38.185 --> 00:24:40.229
You know. it's how
you like to be perceived.

420
00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:42.832
You don't think I'm funny?

421
00:24:42.856 --> 00:24:44.209
Faith. am I funny?

422
00:24:44.233 --> 00:24:46.628
- You're not not funny.
- I mean. you're amusing.

423
00:24:46.652 --> 00:24:49.005
- You're fun to have around.
- That is not the same thing.

424
00:24:49.029 --> 00:24:51.383
You don't think I'm funny. You
think faith is funnier than me?

425
00:24:51.407 --> 00:24:54.284
Leon is lying to you because
he is afraid of telling you the truth.

426
00:24:54.910 --> 00:24:57.222
Faith. that makes sense.

427
00:24:57.246 --> 00:25:00.124
It's not that I'm not funny.
It is that Leon is a coward.

428
00:25:02.001 --> 00:25:04.795
- Did you find anything?
- Yep.

429
00:25:05.546 --> 00:25:07.816
I found this fast-food
receipt from three days ago

430
00:25:07.840 --> 00:25:10.527
during the time that Ronaldo
supposedly disappeared.

431
00:25:10.551 --> 00:25:12.362
He was in Cleveland. Ohio.

432
00:25:12.386 --> 00:25:15.222
And anyone recognize this lipstick?

433
00:25:17.641 --> 00:25:20.578
We found your
cigarettes in Ronaldo's car.

434
00:25:20.602 --> 00:25:22.539
I think that you two were having an affair.

435
00:25:22.563 --> 00:25:24.690
Lila. were you his muse?

436
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:28.420
Sorry. that's what this is about?

437
00:25:28.444 --> 00:25:29.963
I have a solo to rehearse.

438
00:25:29.987 --> 00:25:32.090
What happened?
You break up with him?

439
00:25:32.114 --> 00:25:34.175
He threatened to tell your
husband. so you killed him?

440
00:25:34.199 --> 00:25:37.619
Don't be ridiculous. Stop.
please. Of course we were intimate.

441
00:25:38.412 --> 00:25:42.124
Profoundly. passionately. feverishly.

442
00:25:43.292 --> 00:25:46.563
But it wasn't an affair. because
Tom and I have an arrangement

443
00:25:46.587 --> 00:25:49.566
where we can sleep with whoever
we want as long as no one falls in love.

444
00:25:49.590 --> 00:25:51.443
and believe me. I-I never fall in love.

445
00:25:51.467 --> 00:25:53.570
But not with Ronaldo.

446
00:25:53.594 --> 00:25:56.448
We agreed he was on the no-fly list.

447
00:25:56.472 --> 00:25:58.408
I never agreed to a no-fly list.

448
00:25:58.432 --> 00:26:01.411
That was just something that you
said. and then I did not respond to you.

449
00:26:01.435 --> 00:26:04.438
Can… what does it
matter? The man is dead.

450
00:26:06.732 --> 00:26:08.543
Tom… - hey. hey. buddy.

451
00:26:08.567 --> 00:26:10.211
Just take it easy. okay?

452
00:26:10.235 --> 00:26:12.380
Don't be hysterical. It's pedestrian.

453
00:26:12.404 --> 00:26:14.591
Excuse me. what is going on?

454
00:26:14.615 --> 00:26:16.259
Tom. careful of those hands.

455
00:26:16.283 --> 00:26:18.094
You have to perform tonight.

456
00:26:18.118 --> 00:26:21.473
Do you know anything about why
Ronaldo might have been in Ohio?

457
00:26:21.497 --> 00:26:24.097
We have a receipt putting him
there the day before he was killed.

458
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:26.644
No. I have no idea.

459
00:26:26.668 --> 00:26:29.314
Our relationship wasn't
really based on talking.

460
00:26:32.007 --> 00:26:33.234
Not really your day. man.

461
00:26:33.258 --> 00:26:35.361
- I think I broke it.
- No. that's okay.

462
00:26:35.385 --> 00:26:38.531
Yeah. because you don't
play bass with your feet. Here.

463
00:26:38.555 --> 00:26:39.657
Do you want me to come?

464
00:26:39.681 --> 00:26:42.518
I think you've done enough of that.

465
00:26:43.519 --> 00:26:45.622
Lila. is there anything
else you'd like to share?

466
00:26:45.646 --> 00:26:49.000
I'll just say this. Whatever he was
doing in Ohio. thank god he went.

467
00:26:49.024 --> 00:26:51.294
- Why do you say that?
- Before he disappeared.

468
00:26:51.318 --> 00:26:52.921
he played me what he was working on.

469
00:26:52.945 --> 00:26:54.422
It was atrocious.

470
00:26:54.446 --> 00:26:56.382
We were all going to
be publicly humiliated.

471
00:26:56.406 --> 00:26:58.635
Well. what was he
doing for those two days?

472
00:26:58.659 --> 00:27:00.035
I don't know. He never told me.

473
00:27:00.828 --> 00:27:04.224
All I know is I now have
an exquisite violin solo.

474
00:27:04.248 --> 00:27:07.519
It's gonna be… it's gonna
be career-making. really.

475
00:27:07.543 --> 00:27:10.772
and you should all come
if you can get tickets.

476
00:27:10.796 --> 00:27:13.525
I've given my comps away.
but. look. I-If you'd excuse me.

477
00:27:13.549 --> 00:27:16.176
I-I would really like to rehearse. So…

478
00:27:20.597 --> 00:27:21.908
I don't know about you. faith.

479
00:27:21.932 --> 00:27:25.143
but I… …think it's time for
Franklin to go on a date.

480
00:27:26.019 --> 00:27:27.914
Absolutely not.

481
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:33.211
This was Ronaldo's composition?

482
00:27:33.235 --> 00:27:34.796
Up until two days ago. yes.

483
00:27:34.820 --> 00:27:37.239
Lila was right. It is very…

484
00:27:38.407 --> 00:27:39.467
Amateurish.

485
00:27:39.491 --> 00:27:40.677
I mean. I do not understand

486
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:43.054
how this became the
composition that Ronaldo turned in.

487
00:27:43.078 --> 00:27:46.015
- Do they resemble each other at all?
- No. not even close.

488
00:27:46.039 --> 00:27:49.042
That is like it was written by
an entirely different person.

489
00:27:50.168 --> 00:27:52.981
Maybe he stole it and
that's why he ended up dead.

490
00:27:53.005 --> 00:27:56.067
Lord. never underestimate
the audacity of a straight male

491
00:27:56.091 --> 00:27:57.968
with an inflated ego
and a full head of hair.

492
00:27:59.720 --> 00:28:02.824
No. no. no. I know
you're not laughing now.

493
00:28:02.848 --> 00:28:04.993
So now the man thinks I'm funny?

494
00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:08.520
Tell me the truth.

495
00:28:11.607 --> 00:28:12.649
I don't want kids.

496
00:28:13.692 --> 00:28:15.503
- I know that.
- I like my life. I like my freedom.

497
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.338
- I do not need kids.
- I specifically said

498
00:28:17.362 --> 00:28:19.442
- I'm okay without having kids.
- But you were lying.

499
00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:22.093
Either to me or to yourself. okay?

500
00:28:22.117 --> 00:28:24.721
And it just felt like you thought
that you could wear me down

501
00:28:24.745 --> 00:28:26.931
if you stayed with me long enough.
but I wasn't gonna change my mind.

502
00:28:26.955 --> 00:28:28.707
- Again. I specifically said...
- Benjamin.

503
00:28:29.458 --> 00:28:31.936
You know what. I never should've
trusted you with my first name.

504
00:28:31.960 --> 00:28:34.588
Be honest. Benjamin Franklin.

505
00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:38.818
- Here we go.
- You want them. You do. It's okay.

506
00:28:38.842 --> 00:28:40.153
But god help us.

507
00:28:40.177 --> 00:28:42.989
if there was a child anywhere
near where we were having brunch.

508
00:28:43.013 --> 00:28:45.575
they were the only
ones getting eye contact.

509
00:28:45.599 --> 00:28:47.035
I did that maybe once.

510
00:28:50.687 --> 00:28:52.356
Fine.

511
00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:54.858
I shouldn't have ghosted you.

512
00:28:55.567 --> 00:28:58.528
I actually can't believe
that I did that. It was very…

513
00:29:00.489 --> 00:29:01.657
Immature.

514
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:07.079
Let me make it up to you.

515
00:29:08.455 --> 00:29:11.225
Come to the performance
tonight? I got you a comp ticket.

516
00:29:11.249 --> 00:29:13.436
- Really?
- That's right. Best seat in the house.

517
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:14.461
Wow.

518
00:29:15.295 --> 00:29:16.922
I'd really love to have you there.

519
00:29:18.048 --> 00:29:20.050
Maybe we can be friends?

520
00:29:22.094 --> 00:29:23.095
Okay.

521
00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:24.721
Okay.

522
00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:40.362
It's you. Will Trent.

523
00:29:41.321 --> 00:29:43.216
The man who caught James ulster.

524
00:29:43.240 --> 00:29:45.784
This is your work. is it not?

525
00:29:47.035 --> 00:29:48.245
- Yep.
- You claim

526
00:29:48.829 --> 00:29:50.556
to be a student of James ulster.

527
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:52.725
I'm more than a student. I'm an acolyte.

528
00:29:52.749 --> 00:29:57.129
And you think your work
celebrates James ulster?

529
00:29:57.879 --> 00:30:00.966
You know what I see when I look at this?

530
00:30:02.092 --> 00:30:03.695
It's a cheap knockoff.

531
00:30:03.719 --> 00:30:08.032
This work is meant to be relished.

532
00:30:08.056 --> 00:30:11.077
All I see here

533
00:30:11.101 --> 00:30:15.731
is fear. hesitation. a lack of discipline.

534
00:30:16.314 --> 00:30:18.358
- What is this?
- It's an assessment.

535
00:30:20.152 --> 00:30:22.029
It's a grade. really.

536
00:30:23.155 --> 00:30:24.322
Now. let's see.

537
00:30:26.116 --> 00:30:28.744
C-minus.

538
00:30:29.661 --> 00:30:31.222
And that's being generous.

539
00:30:31.246 --> 00:30:33.516
It's soulless.

540
00:30:34.708 --> 00:30:35.792
Yeah.

541
00:30:36.918 --> 00:30:39.838
Did you even enjoy it?

542
00:30:40.756 --> 00:30:44.843
Did you get a rush? An erection. even?

543
00:30:45.427 --> 00:30:48.906
No. no. no. no. no. I
don't think you did. No. no.

544
00:30:48.930 --> 00:30:52.118
I think you were scared.

545
00:30:52.142 --> 00:30:53.310
I was afraid I'd get caught.

546
00:30:53.935 --> 00:30:55.228
I could tell.

547
00:30:58.774 --> 00:31:02.360
When you're doing work in my name.

548
00:31:03.403 --> 00:31:04.404
it has to be worthy.

549
00:31:06.698 --> 00:31:09.910
I speak through will Trent now.

550
00:31:10.744 --> 00:31:12.621
He's the closest thing I have to a son.

551
00:31:13.914 --> 00:31:16.350
- But she said...
- my daughter.

552
00:31:16.374 --> 00:31:17.459
She's nobody.

553
00:31:18.043 --> 00:31:23.691
You… you were scammed.

554
00:31:23.715 --> 00:31:26.235
I hope you didn't give her
your social security number.

555
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:27.320
I don't understand.

556
00:31:27.344 --> 00:31:30.263
Well. that's as clear as a
bell. you unwashed simpleton.

557
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:35.435
Sit up straight when you talk to me.

558
00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:41.000
My name. my legacy. is
being polluted by this bitch.

559
00:31:41.024 --> 00:31:43.026
and you and I are gonna
stop her blasphemy.

560
00:31:44.111 --> 00:31:48.323
Or I could just sit here

561
00:31:49.241 --> 00:31:53.679
and remove your fingernails one
by one until you come to your senses.

562
00:31:53.703 --> 00:31:57.809
No one… no one will stop
me. I mean. they love me here.

563
00:31:57.833 --> 00:32:00.669
They can't get enough of will Trent.

564
00:32:02.254 --> 00:32:03.880
Are you starting to see…

565
00:32:05.841 --> 00:32:08.552
Why I chose this guy as my vessel?

566
00:32:12.180 --> 00:32:13.890
How can I help you. Mr. Ulster?

567
00:32:16.434 --> 00:32:17.602
Tell me…

568
00:32:19.229 --> 00:32:21.565
What is Adelaide…

569
00:32:22.607 --> 00:32:23.650
Doing?

570
00:32:26.278 --> 00:32:31.092
I don't know. She don't talk to me… no?

571
00:32:31.116 --> 00:32:33.326
I get my instructions
from somebody else.

572
00:32:35.704 --> 00:32:36.955
His name is the commander.

573
00:32:39.249 --> 00:32:41.960
And how do I talk to the commander?

574
00:32:45.630 --> 00:32:48.985
They'll only listen if they
hear it d-directly from me.

575
00:32:50.510 --> 00:32:51.845
Well.

576
00:32:52.846 --> 00:32:54.306
arrange a meeting.

577
00:32:56.808 --> 00:32:58.977
Yeah.

578
00:33:06.443 --> 00:33:07.503
Damn.

579
00:33:08.612 --> 00:33:11.281
That is very hot.

580
00:33:12.032 --> 00:33:14.492
- Now your turn.
- Okay.

581
00:33:15.744 --> 00:33:17.370
Okay.

582
00:33:18.538 --> 00:33:21.475
Now if you raise your gun.
you have to be ready to use it.

583
00:33:21.499 --> 00:33:23.519
- Always aim for center mass.
- Okay.

584
00:33:23.543 --> 00:33:26.355
- Okay. Feet.
- Feet.

585
00:33:26.379 --> 00:33:28.215
- Shoulders.
- Shoulders.

586
00:33:28.798 --> 00:33:31.384
Okay. Breathe.

587
00:33:32.719 --> 00:33:35.931
visualize. and shoot.

588
00:33:39.601 --> 00:33:42.663
- My god.
- Attagirl. You did it.

589
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:44.332
I'm gonna look into
getting one for myself.

590
00:33:44.356 --> 00:33:45.815
Well. let's do it now.

591
00:33:49.027 --> 00:33:52.089
Listen. Casey. I got a
bad feeling about Dallas.

592
00:33:52.113 --> 00:33:53.841
- You need protection.
- You're right.

593
00:33:53.865 --> 00:33:56.886
I just want to do a little
research first. but I promise I will.

594
00:33:56.910 --> 00:33:57.970
Well. just take mine.

595
00:33:57.994 --> 00:33:59.472
I can't. You need it for work.

596
00:33:59.496 --> 00:34:01.289
No. No. no. no. This is my personal gun.

597
00:34:01.998 --> 00:34:05.353
I mean… …you've already shown
that you're comfortable with it.

598
00:34:05.377 --> 00:34:07.730
Listen. hang on to it till you get your own.

599
00:34:07.754 --> 00:34:09.256
Put it somewhere safe.

600
00:34:12.259 --> 00:34:13.551
Thank you. Amanda.

601
00:34:14.219 --> 00:34:17.323
Look. you're in my office.

602
00:34:17.347 --> 00:34:18.658
Yeah. low blood sugar.

603
00:34:18.682 --> 00:34:21.869
But. I have to say. I like it in
here. It's quiet. great snacks.

604
00:34:21.893 --> 00:34:25.998
Yeah. okay. don't get too
comfortable. Who's on the phone?

605
00:34:26.022 --> 00:34:29.502
I'm on hold with the archive
library at Ronaldo's music school.

606
00:34:29.526 --> 00:34:33.339
Turns out that this fast-food restaurant
he visited was only 20 miles from there.

607
00:34:33.363 --> 00:34:35.174
Traffic cameras put him at the campus.

608
00:34:35.198 --> 00:34:37.117
- Nice.
- Hi. Yeah.

609
00:34:38.952 --> 00:34:40.745
Wow.

610
00:34:41.746 --> 00:34:44.874
Ronaldo checked out a
master's thesis from 25 years ago.

611
00:35:14.154 --> 00:35:17.073
Excuse me.

612
00:35:18.783 --> 00:35:20.094
I am at the symphony. What?

613
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:22.263
Ronaldo stole the
composition from Claudia.

614
00:35:22.287 --> 00:35:23.347
What?

615
00:35:23.371 --> 00:35:25.266
We're thinking after she
heard the first rehearsal.

616
00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:27.184
she realized what he'd
done. confronted him.

617
00:35:27.208 --> 00:35:30.354
and when he didn't come clean. she
followed him to the motel and killed him.

618
00:35:30.378 --> 00:35:32.064
Geez. her seat's right next to mine.

619
00:35:32.088 --> 00:35:35.234
Good. Keep an eye on her. We're on our
way to the symphony hall now with backup.

620
00:35:35.258 --> 00:35:36.259
You got it.

621
00:35:53.985 --> 00:35:55.111
Claudia!

622
00:36:18.551 --> 00:36:21.096
Claudia. Come out.

623
00:36:23.515 --> 00:36:25.767
Shh. They're playing right above us.

624
00:36:47.163 --> 00:36:50.667
Claudia. I see you.

625
00:37:16.818 --> 00:37:21.257
Claudia sobinsky. you're under
arrest for the murder of Ronaldo benetti.

626
00:37:21.281 --> 00:37:24.033
Quiet. This is the best part.

627
00:37:32.876 --> 00:37:36.504
Twenty-five years ago. I
showed this piece to Ronaldo.

628
00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:40.467
and he convinced me it wasn't any good.

629
00:37:42.260 --> 00:37:45.263
I was so young and insecure.

630
00:37:47.015 --> 00:37:48.516
I believed him.

631
00:37:52.103 --> 00:37:53.855
But I hear it now.

632
00:37:57.317 --> 00:37:59.152
I was good.

633
00:38:04.449 --> 00:38:05.825
Yes.

634
00:38:06.493 --> 00:38:07.494
You were.

635
00:38:15.668 --> 00:38:20.089
Please just let me listen until the end.

636
00:38:22.342 --> 00:38:24.219
Then I promise I'll go peacefully.

637
00:39:04.843 --> 00:39:06.928
Come on through. We gotta go.

638
00:39:39.335 --> 00:39:40.461
Leon was right.

639
00:39:41.379 --> 00:39:42.439
I do want that.

640
00:39:42.463 --> 00:39:46.009
The husband. the kid. all of it.

641
00:39:47.135 --> 00:39:49.304
Yeah. it's pretty great.

642
00:39:49.888 --> 00:39:50.889
Yeah.

643
00:40:09.073 --> 00:40:10.116
I'm sorry. can I help you?

644
00:40:10.909 --> 00:40:12.327
Jeb says ulster speaks through you.

645
00:40:14.412 --> 00:40:15.413
Right.

646
00:40:16.164 --> 00:40:18.082
You are the commander.

647
00:40:20.043 --> 00:40:21.812
Adelaide must really trust you.

648
00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:23.338
We understand each other.

649
00:40:24.505 --> 00:40:26.191
She helped me see what real freedom is.

650
00:40:26.215 --> 00:40:27.216
Killing?

651
00:40:28.760 --> 00:40:29.945
Hurting innocent people?

652
00:40:29.969 --> 00:40:32.805
No one is innocent.

653
00:40:35.642 --> 00:40:38.728
I know what it's like to be angry.

654
00:40:39.854 --> 00:40:43.149
There are days. more
than I'd like to admit.

655
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:47.236
when I think my anger
might consume me.

656
00:40:49.238 --> 00:40:54.970
But killing doesn't make
you feel free or powerful.

657
00:40:54.994 --> 00:40:57.872
no matter who it is or why.

658
00:40:59.874 --> 00:41:01.793
It eats away at your soul.

659
00:41:06.130 --> 00:41:07.131
What's your name?

660
00:41:09.592 --> 00:41:10.593
Hey.

661
00:41:11.135 --> 00:41:14.573
If you know where Antonio
morales is. you need to tell me now.

662
00:41:15.682 --> 00:41:18.202
Don't let Adelaide get
you into any more trouble.

663
00:41:18.226 --> 00:41:20.645
Yeah. she said you'd try to save me.

664
00:41:23.648 --> 00:41:25.483
- What's this?
- We'll be in touch.

665
00:41:27.110 --> 00:41:31.155
If you follow me. I will tell her.

666
00:41:32.365 --> 00:41:33.783
And if that happens.

667
00:41:34.784 --> 00:41:36.703
I'm not sure what she'll do to Antonio.

668
00:41:38.955 --> 00:41:39.956
Talk soon.

669
00:41:56.305 --> 00:41:59.243
- Casey.
- Amanda. he's here!

670
00:41:59.267 --> 00:42:01.620
- Who? Dallas?
- He's in the house!

671
00:42:01.644 --> 00:42:03.455
Go get the gun.
Remember what I taught you.

672
00:42:03.479 --> 00:42:05.624
Come back here. you
bitch! I'm gonna kill you.

673
00:42:07.233 --> 00:42:09.628
I-I'm sending the cops.
You know. ju-just hold tight.

674
00:42:09.652 --> 00:42:11.195
No. no!

675
00:42:13.114 --> 00:42:14.174
Casey?

675
00:42:15.305 --> 00:43:15.922
Do you want subtitles for any video?
